Pep Organ

Orlando Gibbons (1583-1625) is a composer I love coming back to every now and then. His keyboard works truly show a high level of craft and creativity that still maintains their excitement today.

This Voluntary (also known as a Fancy, the old English word for Fantasia) has several sections which are guided by their use of different melodies, and which I highlight by a few stop changes. I decided the open the work with just four foot stops, to evoke the flavour of the Renaissance organ, and the organ at St Stephen's Uniting Church seems to have achieved this effect surprisingly well. I love the way that the right hand often rises and falls in one long sigh, such as at 1:16. ...

Pep Organ
